<TEXT>
here are some of the major figures sent here in 
recent months to face drug charges 
luis arce gomez a colonel dubbed the minister of cocaine 
while serving as bolivias interior minister in 198081 arrested 
by bolivian authorities dec 10 and turned over to face a 1983 
cocaine conspiracy indictment by a miami grand jury that alleged he 
charged traffickers protection money 
arraigned on wednesday being held without bond in a federal 
prison south of here a 1983 us effort to extradite him from 
argentina failed when he was released from custody there 
eduardo martinez romero 36 a reputed financial wizard behind 
the medellin cocaine cartel flown to atlanta on sept 6 the first 
person extradited from colombia in its current crackdown 
being held in isolation at the federal penitentiary in atlanta 
to face federal charges there he laundered 12 billion in drug 
money 
jose rafael abellosilva 35 flown to tulsa okla after his 
oct 29 extradition from colombia 
first indicted in 1987 a federal grand jury in tulsa this week 
handed down an amended indictment tying him to cocaine conspiracies 
with reputed colombian cocaine kingpins pablo escobargaviria 
jorge ochoavasquez and the late jose gonzalo rodriguezgacha 
assistant us attorney david omeilia said in tulsa that abello 
is the most significant defendant in american custody linked to 
the cartel 
victor eduardo meramosquera 36 a convicted cocaine 
smuggler turned over to us marshals by colombian authorities 
dec 24 and flown to new york 
mistakenly released from federal detention in new york and fled 
to colombia before his trial in 1984 convicted in absentia of drug 
conspiracy and distribution and faces up to 30 years in prison 
faces trial on a subsequent charge of codirecting the us 
operations of a continuing drug enterprise that smuggled more than 
2200 pounds of cocaine into the united states 
guillermo juan bueno delgado 54 a colombian hotel owner and 
investor flown to tallahassee on nov 4 faces 1985 cocaine 
indictments in florida california and illinois alleging 
involvement in cocaine conspiracies 
roberto peter carliniarrico 38 taken from colombia to 
orlando on oct 14 to face 1986 federal and state charges of 
racketeering and conspiracy alleging he helped smuggle more than a 
ton of cocaine into the united states 
pleaded guilty wednesday to federal smuggling count but still 
faces the state charges 
bernardo pelaez roldan taken to detroit on oct 14 convicted 
in absentia there in 1984 on conspiracy to possess cocaine with 
intent to distribute 
ana rodriguez de tamayo 50 a colombian taken to miami on 
oct 14 codefendant of arce gomez on the 1983 charges pleaded 
guilty tuesday to conspiracy to import cocaine 
luis del cid a former panama defense forces captain described 
as noriegas righthand man surrendered to us forces in panama 
on dec 25 and faces charges here in the noriega indictment 
also brought here since the us invasion was a panamanian 
pilot daniel miranda who is a noriega codefendant and a federal 
investigator said another panamanian codefendant eduardo pardo 
was arrested wednesday in panama 
in 1987 us authorities were delighted by the extradition of 
colombian cocaine kingpin carlos lehder rivas taken to the united 
states on feb 4 1987 after a shootout at a jungle hideout 
after a federal trial in jacksonville lehder 40 was convicted 
of conspiracy cocaine importation operating a continuing criminal 
enterprise and eight counts of possession of cocaine with intent to 
distribute 
sentenced in 1988 to life in prison without the possibility of 
parole plus 135 years being held in the federal prison in marion 
ill 
