the regional american red cross is asking 
hospitals in southeastern pennsylvania and southern new jersey to 
cancel all elective surgery because of a critically low supply of 
blood 
the request was to go to 93 hospitals in the region said susan 
snyder a spokeswoman for the pennjersey region of american red 
cross blood services 
the hospitals will all be advised that we cant support 
elective surgeries she said thursday 
in georgia four atlantaarea hospitals also canceled elective 
surgeries because of low blood supplies 
elective surgery includes operations that may be necessary to a 
patients health but not those needed to save a life 
ms snyder said surgeries have been canceled previously because 
of blood shortages but there havent been cancellations this 
severe such extensive and planned cancellation of elective surgery 
in at least 10 years 
the request came on the second day of an emergency appeal for 
blood donors as the red cross said it fell 4500 units short during 
december and had virtually no blood available of types o negative 
and b negative 
donation levels typically drop during the holiday season but 
they were reduced even further when the unusually cold december 
kept people from going to donation centers the red cross said 
the red cross which provides 94 percent of the blood used in 
the 93 hospitals needs about 1750 donors a day and was down to 
about 1000 last month 
donors increased to 1347 wednesday and more callers were 
seeking information thursday the red cross said 
the initial response we are seeing is very gratifying said 
dr william c sherwood director of the pennjersey region 
in atlanta surgeries were delayed for a pregnant woman needing 
abdominal surgery a man awaiting openheart surgery a patient 
waiting for a liver transplant and a patient with a bleeding 
ulcer anne willcox a red cross representative said thursday 
after an appeal for donations about 1300 people donated blood 
wednesday red cross officials said but that response was not 
matched thursday 
the red cross normally needs 900 units of blood a day to meet 
the demands of the more than 100 hospitals in the 82county atlanta 
region but donations dropped as low as 300 units a day over the 
holidays said beth v greenberg administrative director of red 
cross donor services 
