the pennsylvania crime commission has reported that he was 
deported in 1958 as an illegal alien but returned to the united 
states married a cousin and settled in new york 
the indictment said john gambino identified as giovanni in the 
indictment and his brother were in charge of a gambino family crew 
that operated out of a cafe in brooklyn 
since at least 1978 the sicilian and american branches of the 
mafia conducted a joint venture to import multiple kilogram 
quantities of heroin into the united states through giovanni 
gambino and his subordinates in new york the indictment said 
as an example the indictment said gambino and his crew 
allegedly received more than 500 kilograms 1100 pounds of 
heroin from the sicilian mafia between late 1978 and mid1979 
gambinos attorney robert ellis opposed his clients 
detention saying he had serious health problems that date back to 
a stroke in 1985 and open heart surgery in 1987 ellis said gambino 
works in the construction industry 
if convicted of the charges gambino could be sentenced to life 
in prison and fined millions of dollars 
according to the pennsylvania crime commission gambino was one 
of several cousins of carlo gambino who moved in 1972 to southern 
