<TEXT>
president saddam hussein on friday proposed 
resuming peace talks with iran that have been stalled more than a 
year and he suggested the longhostile nations reestablish air 
links 
we are seeking to open a new door for a dignified peace with 
iran saddam said in a speech marking the 69th anniversary of the 
founding of the iraqi army 
he hailed advances by the iraqi arms industry including the 
recent launching of longrange missiles and of a rocket reportedly 
capable of putting a satellite in space 
saddam suggested that direct meetings between representatives of 
iran and iraq be held alternately in tehran and baghdad under the 
auspices of the un secretarygeneral 
fighting in the eightyear iraniraq war ended aug 20 1988 
when both sides accepted a ceasefire based on un security 
council resolution 598 peace talks stalled immediately over 
interpretation of the terms of the resolution and priority in 
implementing its various clauses 
saddam said his proposed dialogue will aim at reaching a 
common understanding of the clauses of resolution 598 and fix a 
timetable for its implementation provided that the talks are 
completed within a period not exceeding three months 
there was no immediate response from iran 
iran has insisted that resumption of talks be preceded by the 
withdrawal of iraqi troops from 1065 square miles of iranian 
territory it claims are still under occupation 
iraq meanwhile wants iran to accept a new border giving iraq 
total control of the shattalarab waterway under a 1975 accord 
the border was drawn down the middle of the waterway which is 
iraqs main outlet to the sea 
saddam proposed an immediate exchange of all wounded and sick 
prisoners of war as the first step in reviving negotiations that 
would be followed by the release of the longestheld pows mainly 
those captured in the early stages of the war he said 
he also called for registering thousands of prisoners who have 
not been included in lists provided to the red cross the agency 
has registered 50182 prisoners held by iran and 19284 by iraq 
but un officials and diplomats say there are at least 100000 
pows held by both sides 
the red cross mediated an agreement to repatriate ailing and 
crippled pows immediately after the ceasefire the agreement 
collapsed after the release of only 400 prisoners as the sides 
accused each other of falsifying the number of captives 
the president said establishing air links between iran and iraq 
would secure an atmosphere of peace and security among the people 
of iran and iraq 
air links between the countries were cut off shortly before the 
war broke out in september 1980 
dealing with the advances in iraqs arms industry saddam 
attacked the united states for expressing concern over new iraqi 
missiles without saying anything about israels nuclear capability 
iraq announced last month it had launched a 48ton threestage 
rocket capable of placing a satellite in space it also said it had 
testfired two surfacetosurface missiles with a range of 1243 
miles long enough to reach israel 
washington confirmed the testfirings 
israel complained the iraqi advances coupled with its 
stockpiling of chemical weapons and reported efforts to acquire a 
nuclear capability posed a serious threat 
citing a similar excuse in 1981 israel launched a longrange 
air raid that destroyed a frenchbuilt nuclear reactor near baghdad 
saddam said iraq will retaliate firmly and with precision to 
