strangled and sexually molested while visiting watertown 
shawcross also confessed to strangling 10yearold john blake 
of watertown according to retired watertown police detective 
charles kubinski who interrogated shawcross about the killings 
shawcross was paroled from green haven state prison in june 1987 
and appeared to be adapting well to life outside prison edward 
elwin executive director of the state division of parole said 
today 
superficially he was making a good adjustment elwin said 
shawcross had tried to settle in delhi in rural delaware 
county following his parole but was moved by parole officials to 
rochester after about two weeks when residents complained about his 
presence 
investigators first questioned shawcross wednesday while they 
were searching for a missing woman west of rochester according to 
news reports searchers found one womans body in the area 
wednesday afternoon and a second womans body thursday 
when the suspect was brought in again for questioning thursday 
he confessed to 10 of the killings according to rochester 
television station wokr which quoted unidentified police sources 
