carhenge the junk car sculpture that 
spoofs englands prehistoric stonehenge has a better chance of 
survival because of a city council vote 
the tourist attraction was threatened because its creator never 
fully complied with a special use permit granted when he built it 
outside this northwestern nebraska town in 1987 officials said 
the city council voted thursday to exempt the 106acre site 
from the city zoning boundaries councilman mike dafney said by 
adjusting the boundary the city dissociates itself from carhenge 
built by james reinders of houston 
it can get on with itself and try to survive by itself he 
said but the city has no liability i can see or anything else 
we more or less are washing our hands with it as far as trying to 
regulate it 
however the city planning commission still has to approve the 
change 
the sculpture consists of old car bodies arranged in a likeness 
of the famed stonehenge in england 
reinders reportedly never fully complied with the permit which 
included requirements for liability insurance a paved access an 
escrow account for maintenance and a parking area for visitors at 
carhenge 
a group called friends of carhenge has been working to bring the 
growing tourist attraction into compliance with the permit 
