<TEXT>
socialism is not to blame for chinas poverty 
and the nation will eventually triumph over its capitalist rivals 
the communist party daily newspaper said friday 
the lengthy commentary in the peoples daily came less than a 
month after a small group of university students in a bold gesture 
of dissent unfurled a banner in front of the state television 
station reading motherland why are you so poor 
it is also part of a government propaganda campaign to convince 
the populace that china must stick to the socialist road suppress 
political dissent and reject the reforms now sweeping east europe 
the dec 9 rally by beijing university of aeronautics students 
the first in the capital since the military crushed the 
prodemocracy movement last spring was not reported in the 
official press 
but chinese sources said 10 seniors were arrested including 
three who were only indirectly involved in the demonstration they 
said one chinese reporter who tried to stop police from hitting the 
protesters was also detained 
one source said a relative of one of the students was told he 
was taken to qincheng a highsecurity prison where student 
activists from the democracy movement are being held 
the commentary while not mentioning the protest said many 
young people are asking if the socialist system is superior why 
is socialist china now so poor 
it acknowledged that a per capita income of about 300 a year 
makes china one of the worlds poor countries with a rank below 
100th in the world 
but it attributed that to the nations huge population of 11 
billion and noted that china ranks eighth in the world in gross 
national product and is one of the worlds leading political 
economic and military powers 
it said the cost of goods is low distribution of income is 
equitable calorie intake approaches world averages and the 
average lifespan is 69 years compared to 63 in the world as a 
whole 
the daily said it was unfair to compare china to japan or 
taiwan saying the rapid postwar development of those capitalist 
economies shows the inferiority of socialism 
both japan and taiwan it said started with more solid economic 
bases and received substantial assistance from the united states 
chiang kaisheks nationalists also carried off great quantities of 
gold when they fled to taiwan in 1949 it said 
the commentary said chinas economy grew 94 percent a year from 
1967 to 1984 compared with 49 percent for the worlds developing 
countries and that the gap with developed nations was shrinking 
it also emphasized the moral superiority of socialism 
whatever happens it said quoting senior leader deng xiaoping 
capitalism cannot cast off the super profits of the millionaires 
cannot break away from exploitation and plunder cannot shake off 
economic crises cannot form a common ideal and morality and cannot 
avoid every type of extreme and serious crime degeneracy and 
despair 
china is backward it concluded but there will be the day 
when we approach catch up with and surpass those developed 
capitalist countries time belongs to us and the final victory 
belongs to us 
