attorney general dick thornburgh has urged 
us attorneys around the country to choose experienced prosecutors 
to fill vacancies on the organized crime strike forces being 
transferred to their offices a spokesman said friday 
the strike forces which operated for 22 years as field offices 
of the justice department have lost 33 attorneys nearly a quarter 
