likely to depart now that a year of controversy and objections from 
congress have failed to block the merger 
departing strike force attorneys and former justice officials 
said the merger was unattractive to many mob prosecutors because 
the us attorneys appointed by the president tend to concentrate 
on shorterterm cases with quick impact and publicity rather than 
the complex longterm investigations used during the last two 
decades to imprison the mob leadership in more than 11 eleven major 
cities 
thornburgh imposed the change which he has sought since he was 
us attorney in pittsburgh 15 years ago on new years day 
justice spokesman dave runkel said thornburgh spoke at an 
allday meeting in a suburban motel with the strike force chiefs 
affected us attorneys and members of the criminal divisions 
organized crime and racketeering section 
the meeting thursday was closed to the public 
the attorney general stressed the need for the us attorneys 
to put experienced prosecutors in vacant spots on the strike forces 
prosecutors who previously worked on sensitive and complex 
cases runkel said and the us attorneys reported that that 
is exactly what they are doing where there are vacancies 
some 115 strike force positions are being turned into assistant 
us attorney posts committed to working on organized crime 
another 20 attorneys are being recruited to join a squad in 
washington available to handle emergency assignments around the 
country 
runkel said that of the 135 slots 116 are filled and five more 
attorneys are in the process of being hired 
runkel said thursdays meeting went well 
everybodys committed to making this system work he said 
there may be some who felt there wasnt a need for this change 
now but all recognize that the change has occurred 
he said thornburgh and other top officials who addressed the 
planning session stressed that they want organized crime 
investigations carried out as vigorously in the future as in the 
past 
thornburgh has said the move was needed to end turf battles 
between strike force chiefs and us attorneys and to address to 
forms of organized crime such as colombian drug lords and street 
gangs 
the only hot point came when i spoke and gave them advice on 
how to handle the press runkel said declining to elaborate 
the strike forces operated in 14 headquarters cities and 11 
suboffice cities they are being merged with 23 us attorney 
offices that cover the same areas 
