<TEXT>
president bush on friday granted poland more 
dutyfree access to us markets saying the move will open the 
door for investment trade and the interaction of two free 
peoples 
in a white house ceremony bush signed a proclamation which 
should provide typical savings of between 3 and 10 percent for the 
producers of polish exports into the united states 
the presidents action qualified poland for concessionary trade 
rules known as the generalized system of preferences under which 
duties are lifted on about half of the products on the us tariff 
schedule in polands case the benefit would apply to about 
onefourth of the goods subject to duties it now sends to the 
united states 
this means that polish exports will enjoy the most liberal 
access possible to the american market bush said and it will 
pave the way for increases in polish exports to the united states 
a vital contribution to polands economic recovery 
the past year has been one of outstanding change in eastern 
europe the president said but it was the brave people of 
poland under the banner of solidarity that led the way poland 
has blazed the trail the freedom trail 
bush addressed a small audience that included secretary of state 
james a baker iii trade ambassador carla hills and polands 
ambassador jan kinast 
in addition to the new trade concessions bush noted the us 
government is committed to a threeyear economic assistance program 
to poland totaling 1 billion and has already contributed 200 
million in aid since last spring the western alliance has promised 
more than 8 billion in economic aid to poland over the threeyear 
period 
poland previously was granted mostfavorednation trading status 
by the united states meaning its products qualified for the lower 
tariffs accorded us allies the new designation allows many of 
those same goods to enter the country without paying the tariffs 
charged developed countries on the mostfavorednation list 
the concession does not guarantee sales in the united states 
but is designed to provide a savings margin that could prove 
decisive on the american market and thus spur increased trading 
activity about 50 million in polish goods already enter the 
united states dutyfree 
administration officials said that by volume the polish 
products likely to benefit the most include tractors and parts 
furniture cutting tools machine tools titanium dioxide and 
copper wire duties for those goods now range from 22 percent to 
72 percent 
the concession also would benefit several polish products on 
which high duties ranging between 17 percent to 45 percent now 
are charged vodka and other alcoholic beverages cork products 
brussels sprouts preserved vegetables and clincial thermometers 
based on 1988 trade data dutiable polish products worth 733 
million were imported into the united states in categories for 
which tariffs now will be lifted that would amount to a potential 
savings based on that years volume of 35 million 
if poland fully utilized its latest eligibility its trading 
volume under the concession would be estimated to rank with that of 
turkey zaire and costa rica 
</TEXT>
