<TEXT>
more than 720000 ethnic germans 
resettled in west germany in 1989 nearly half of them from east 
germany the interior ministry said friday 
it was the largest immigration of ethnic germans to west germany 
in the countrys 40year history the largest group were young 
skilled workers fleeing east germany at the start of the 
prodemocracy movement last year 
the interior ministry said 343854 east germans arrived in west 
germany in 1988 the number was 39832 
the number of arrivals of ethnic germans from other eastern 
european countries last year was 377055 the ministry said 
compared with 202673 in 1988 
of this years emigrants 250340 came from poland 93134 from 
the soviet union and 23387 from romania the remainder came from 
czechoslovakia hungary and yugoslavia the ministry report said 
east germans and ethnic east european germans resettling in west 
germany are automatically granted citizenship 
the flood of east germans to west germany began last summer 
after hungary began dismantling its border barriers with austria 
prompting east germans to cross from hungary through austria to the 
west 
tens of thousands of east germans seeking legal passage to west 
germany then began crowding west german embassies in hungary 
poland and czechoslovakia 
the exodus and subsequent prodemocracy rallies drew hundreds of 
thousands to the streets of major east german cities and forced the 
opening of the borders 
</TEXT>
