<TEXT>
the 11yearold war in afghanistan has 
destroyed much of the countrys agrarian economy and helped turn 
its small centuriesold tradition of poppy cultivation into a 
multimillion dollar industry 
officials say the colorful flowers sticky yield of opium is 
being refined into heroin powder in remote laboratories along the 
mountainous pakistanafghanistan frontier and shipped to the west 
western narcotics agents estimate that as much as 80 percent of 
the heroin sold in europe and 25 percent sold in the united states 
comes now from the region the remainder is from mexico and the 
golden triangle of southeast asia experts say 
afghan aid a british emergency relief organization began a 
program last june of offering agricultural incentives in hopes of 
weaning farmers away from opium poppies in rebelcontrolled areas 
the united states which has spent billions of dollars as the 
main arms supplier for antigovernment moslem guerrillas plans to 
launch a similar program this year 
no country has felt the effects of the illicit industry more 
than pakistan through which most of the heroin passes on its way 
to the west 
khalim dilkhan chairman of the pakistan narcotics control 
board said local agents in 1988 alone seized 13669 pounds of 
heroin compared with 950 pounds in 1980 
narcotics agents say a kilogram 22 pounds of 97 percent pure 
heroin fetches 1000 at the pakistanafghan border 
multiply that about 100 times for new york city said 
dilkhan 
he said heroin addiction was virtually unknown in pakistan a 
moslem country of 109 million people but now more than a million 
poor mainly urban young pakistanis are hooked 
in 10 years the problem has multiplied a thousand times 
dilkhan said 
no statistics are available on the number of addicts in 
afghanistan and experts do not even hazard a guess 
opium production and to some extent export has existed for 
centuries in afghanistan and what is now pakistan but experts said 
three events in the late 1970s combined to help make heroin a huge 
export industry 
turkeys crackdown on heroin labs operating in eastern 
anatolia which forced production into western iran 
irans islamic revolution which purged corrupt officials who 
had participated in the opium trade 
the war in afghanistan sparked by a marxist coup in 1978 
which has dislocated about half the countrys 15 million people and 
spawned anarchy in the countryside 
soviet combat troops intervened to prop up the marxist 
government in kabul from december of 1979 to last february but the 
ruling peoples democratic party of afghanistan controls only the 
countrys major cities 
almost all the poppy cultivation occurs in areas held by the 
usarmed moslem guerrillas the mujahedeen or holy warriors 
where farmers once raised wheat corn and barley 
experts say these are the areas that have been hit hardest by 
artillery shelling and aerial bombing 
the main thing is the destruction of the irrigation systems 
opium poppy takes very little water said peter rees afghan 
aids field director in the frontier city of peshawar 
the major mujahedeen groups which are headquartered in 
pakistan acknowledge that some of their local commanders are 
involved in poppy cultivation however the leaders of those groups 
deny that they condone it 
in some areas there must be some benefit to mujahedeen 
commanders said rees but ive seen no clear evidence to show 
that high commanders are involved 
pakistani and us narcotics experts based in pakistan say they 
agree with that assessment 
afghan aids program offers assistance in the form of advice and 
development projects to farmers mainly in afghanistans eastern 
nangarhar province who sign contracts promising not to grow poppy 
in the spring well go and monitor each and every 
recipient rees said im reasonably confident theyll uphold 
these contracts 
the us congress has approved 125 million for a similar 
threeyear program to be run by the us agency for international 
development in consultation with the us drug enforcement 
administration 
