suicide earned him enough laurels to get a shot at a big break 
overseas 
most european directors have the american dream he said 
in the end nonconformists like rainer werner fassbinder also 
wanted an oscar when youre in your bed at night you just see 
yourself standing there on a us movie set 
last february and march he stood on an american set and the 
reality was sobering it is the just the same as working here 
youre only making a movie 
but he had to cut his original plans for shooting bandini in 
11 weeks down to seven after he could only raise 4 million instead 
of 6 million 
as a result the schedule was so tight the hours so long he once 
fell asleep on the set during the last week by then however he 
had already accomplished a tinsel town rarity he stayed within the 
budget and the deadline 
it was a miracle deruddere said crediting the tiny 
european budgets that forced an iron discipline upon him in his 
early days only halfmockingly he was told he could become a star 
in hollywood simply on that merit 
but deruddere wants to be an artist not an employee 
for that reason he rejected a 15 million offer from american 
producers to direct bandini provided he relinquished a final 
say in the production had he accepted he said the films story 
line would have been too sweet i wanted to make an emotional 
film not a tearjerker 
set in rocklin colo in 1925 wait until spring bandini 
tells the story of a poor unemployed italian bricklayer who has to 
feed his large family through the winter 
svevo bandini mantegna loses his money to gambling and his 
heart to the rich widow mrs hildegarde dunaway while his wife 
ornella muti prays for his return in the end svevos son 
arturo lures bandini back into the family fold with a couple of 
lies 
it is not such a wholesome theme deruddere said the 
family comes back together because of the lie the end is very 
ambiguous 
central to the story is an italian immigrants american dream 
and his sons musings about baseball and movie stars not the most 
obvious subject for a european director it is not typically 
american because the dream is seen as something unattainable the 
italian immigrants can only hope to belong 
it also helped that the bandini family closely resembled his own 
coming from belgium where just about anything is allowed on the 
set he faced for the first time the strongly regulated us movie 
industry 
the homely amateurism that can be so stimulating does not 
exist there said deruddere whose first task was to find a 
nonunion state in the rockies to shoot his film otherwise the 
movie could never be made 
he settled on utah and location shots were made near salt lake 
city even so utahs child labor laws forced him to work at a 
diabolical rhythm to ensure the young stars were in bed at 
night 
shooting was marred by a lack of snow in the rockies and 
artificial snow had to be used for countless takes but when 
deruddere himself provided a helping hand in the time consuming 
job some jaws dropped 
when the snow was not spread fast enough i just got on the 
truck to help some people freaked out and pointed look at the 
director you could never do a thing like that in hollywood 
but moving to california is not exactly his dream you dont 
have to work there you have to earn respect there 
