womens wing of a high security prison 
the movie centers around the child baris who enters as a baby 
when his mother gets a jail term for a drug peddling offense he 
literally is growing up in jail the practice is common in turkey 
because there are no institutions to care for children of 
imprisoned parents 
the mother is in a ward with women imprisoned for petty crimes 
most of them are illiterate and unable to deal with the bright and 
curious child who is forever asking questions 
in the next ward are political prisoners all university 
students or graduates who take over the education of baris one of 
them inci becomes a special friend to the boy who is heartbroken 
when she is released 
the film is based on a novel by feride cicekoglu an architect 
imprisoned for four years after the 1980 military takeover for 
belonging to an outlawed leftist organization 
it is a real life story director basaran said the character 
inci is based on the author 
many books and several movies have emerged from the prison 
experiences of turkish artists and intellectuals put behind bars 
