the national bank of canada said it had seized 
13 million shares of campeau corp after a company controlled by 
robert campeau defaulted on loans from the bank 
national bank president andre berard said thursday that campeau 
the chairman of the struggling retailing and developing firm had 
personally taken out the loan the amount of which was not 
revealed to purchase stock in campeau corp 
the bank said the 13 million shares which had been held by 
robert campeau represented 29 percentof the voting stock in 
campeau corp 
the banks decision to transfer the stock to its name had 
nothing to do with the recent deterioration in campeau corp 
finances berard said 
its a different matter altogetherl he said in a telephone 
interview 
a campeau corp spokeswoman carole sanger said in cincinnati 
it is a personal situation involving the bank and robert campeau 
and it would be inappropriate for the company to comment a 
reporter calling robert campeaus office in toronto was referred to 
ms sanger 
national bank said it had also seized about 60 million in 
debentures that it held as security and has taken steps to have 
transferred to its name another 4 million of campeau corps 
subordinate preference shares 
the bank said in a statement the shares were provided as 
collateral by robert campeau capital inc and a second company the 
latter firm had received the loan from the national bank 
national bank said its action aims at consolidating its 
position pending the outcome of restructuring negotiations for 
campeaus federated department stores inc and allied stores corp 
in the united states berard said the bank wanted the parties 
involved in those talks to be aware that it now owned the stock 
on tuesday a syndicate of banks led by citibank agreed not to 
declare federated and allied in technical default on 234 billion 
in loans 
the syndicate agreed not to press the point before jan 15 
giving campeau more time to show it is making progressin sorting 
out its financial problems the bankers previously said they might 
ask for full repayment of the loan a demand that presumably could 
have forced campeau to file for protection under us bankruptcy 
laws 
in exchange for the delay federated agreed to pay off a 250 
million bridge loan 
campeau corp which owns 258 stores went heavily into debt to 
buy federated for66 billion in 1988 and to take over allied at a 
cost of 34 billion in 1986 
the company announced in september it was having trouble making 
its interest payments besides the bank loans the company must pay 
interest on approximately 7 billion in highyield junk bonds it 
sold to finance the buyouts 
campeau is trying to sell its star bloomingdales department 
store chain 
national bank said the voting rights on the stock will now be 
exercised by national bank representatives the bank said 
berard said in a statement the bank does not intend to dispose 
of the campeau securities or acquire additional ones 
besides bloomingdales federateds divisions include abraham amp 
strauss burdines lazarus and richs allieds divisions are 
jordan marsh sterns maas jordan marsh florida and the bon 
marche 
