days would have imposed a sales tax on offroad vehicles camping 
equipment motor homes and pleasure boats 
supporters of that rejected proposal wanted to have the new 
revenue earmarked for specific recreation and conservation programs 
on federal lands but it too fell victim to darmans concern that 
critics would charge the president with violating his pledge 
against new taxes 
