<TEXT>
bond corp holdings ltd won a reprieve 
friday as the western australian supreme court dismissed a 
government petition to liquidate the media brewing natural 
resources and property empire 
the court ruled against the state government insurance 
commission which had asked the court to appoint a provisional 
liquidator for bond corp on the grounds that the company 
controlled by financier alan bond was insolvent 
a judge ruled that the insurance commission had failed to prove 
its claim 
there is no evidence that the creditors of bond corp arent 
being paid the judge said 
the future of bond corp may be uncertain the judge said but a 
petition should not be filed on speculation that a company may 
possibly at some time in the future experience severe financial 
difficulties 
he also ruled that a nearly 668000 debt that was the basis of 
the petition was disputed by bond corp 
while bond corp succeeded on one front the company whose 
debts total 56 billion was still battling in another court to 
overturn an order to appoint receivers and managers to its 
australian brewing units 
the company is also trying to negotiate with us holders of 
debentures issued by its bond brewing holdings ltd unit who have 
demanded immediate repayment of 510 million of the securities and 
overdue inerest 
lawyers for the debenture holders said in court here friday they 
intend to support continuation of receivers appointed last month to 
operate bonds brewing units 
