<TEXT>
an alaskan telephone company friday received 
final federal approval for what is believed to be the first direct 
telephone link between alaska and the soviet union 
the federal communications commission said alascom may establish 
as many as 12 twoway uhf radiophone circuits between gambell 
alaska and provideniya magadan the soviet union 
the service began in august after federal authorities gave 
alascom verbal approval to proceed pending final authorization 
according to alascoms washington attorney charles naftalin 
he said several circuits were operating smoothly except for 
occasional technical difficulties on the soviet end 
gambell which is on st lawrence island is only about 62 miles 
from magadan across the bering strait but prior to this new 
service telephone calls between alaska and the soviet far east 
were routed through thousands of miles of land and undersea phone 
lines or satellite relays 
naftalin said it was the first terrestrial link ever between 
the us and soviet union but at this point its only for 
alaskans 
the transmitter at gambell is linked to a satellite ground 
station that can relay telephone signals to an alascom receiving 
station near fairbanks 
but naftalin said its not configured yet to allow both 
nations to generally call back and forth 
in seeking federal permission alascom said a direct link is 
important in light of the strong community of interest between 
alaskans and the soviet far east including close family ties among 
native populations the fcc said 
the commission in finding the new service in the public 
interest and convenience noted that alascoms proposal was 
supported by the state department contingent upon a finding that 
there will be no transfer of equipment that may be used militarily 
alascom will own and supply all transmitting and receiving 
equipment including the equipment installed on the soviet end the 
fcc said 
the fcc previously ruled that alascom could use radio 
frequencies generally reserved for cellular phone services 
the new service will include messaging private line and data 
communications 
</TEXT>
