european community officials may meet 
soon to mull additional aid to romania and to seek normal 
diplomatic relations with that country now that dictator nicolae 
ceausescu has fallen ec officials said friday 
a paper by the european commission the communitys executive 
body also urged the community to financially support economic 
reform efforts in the east and reach trade agreements with those 
countries 
there is a common interest on the part of the community its 
neighbors and all states sharing its fundamental values in ensuring 
that reform in east europe does not founder the paper read 
the paper presented thursday at a meeting of top commission 
officials said a meeting could be held soon to examine romanias 
need for additional assistance from the 12nation trading bloc 
also known as the common market 
in the course of these discussions it will be pointed out to 
the romanian side that the time has come to establish normal 
diplomatic relations with the community according to the 
document 
the paper also stated the common market should be prepared to 
restart negotiations which have been stalled since 1987 on a 
trade and economic cooperation agreement with romania 
the two sides arranged a limited trade pact in industrial 
products in 1980 the community agreed in 1986 to discuss extending 
the arrangement to agricultural products and economic cooperation 
but no serious negotiations were held 
the community has negotiated four tradeexpanding agreements 
with eastern european countries since it established formal ties in 
june 1988 with the socialist economic bloc known as the council 
for mutual economic assistance or comecon 
the common market has wideranging trade and economic 
cooperation accords with poland hungary and the soviet union and a 
smaller pact with czechoslovakia 
the commission document also said the community was close to a 
pact with bulgaria it also said new negotiations with east germany 
should end in an agreement within the first half of the year and 
that informal contacts have been made with czechoslovakia to 
discuss extending its arrangement to trade and economic cooperation 
the paper reflected the communitys growing interest in 
developing strong ties with the emerging democracies in eastern 
europe it has led an effort by two dozen western nations to 
fashion an economic aid program to encourage reforms in hungary and 
poland 
the pace of change in east europe the expectations of the 
peoples concerned and of their governments as well as the 
communitys own interests in the political and economic future of 
europe now require the community to take further initiatives the 
paper read 
