rebalancing 
yeutter explained the concept of tarrification like this at a 
news conference the principal import restrictions around the 
world are nontariff measures the way to deal with that is to 
convert them into tariffs and negotiate those tariffs down 
yeutter called the ecs rebalancing policy to liberalize 
trade restrictions on some products but tighten them in others as 
antithetical to the spirit of the gatt it is a barrier to 
trade i dont see any support for rebalancing outside the ec 
australias kerin agreed saying rebalancing is just another 
denial of market access 
