<TEXT>
bond corp holdings ltd won a reprieve 
friday as the western australian supreme court dismissed a 
government petition to liquidate the media brewing natural 
resources and property empire 
the court ruled against the state government insurance 
commission which had asked the court to appoint a provisional 
liquidator for bond corp on the grounds that the company 
controlled by financier alan bond was insolvent 
a judge ruled that the insurance commission had failed to prove 
its claim 
there is no evidence that the creditors of bond corp arent 
being paid the judge said 
the future of bond corp may be uncertain the judge said but a 
petition should not be filed on speculation that a company may 
possibly at some time in the future experience severe financial 
difficulties 
he also ruled that a nearly 668000 debt that was the basis of 
the petition was disputed by bond corp 
bond corp executive director peter lucas called the court 
decision a resounding victory for the company 
while bond corp succeeded on one front the company whose 
debts total 56 billion was still battling in another court to 
overturn an order to appoint receivers and managers to its 
australian brewing units 
the company is also trying to negotiate with us holders of 
debentures issued by its bond brewing holdings ltd unit who have 
demanded immediate repayment of 510 million of the securities and 
overdue interest 
lawyers for the debenture holders said in court here friday they 
intend to support continuation of receivers appointed last month to 
operate bonds brewing units 
the court appointed the receivers at the request of a syndicate 
of international banks led by national australia bank ltd 
us noteholders were due to receive a 3219 million interest 
payment from bonds brewing arm but the courts froze that payment 
at the request of the bank syndicate bond brewing has asked the 
court to lift the banks stoppayment notice 
alan bond who controls about 58 percent of bond corp gained 
virtual hero status in australia when he won the 1983 americas cup 
yachting trophy the millionaire industrialist has been selling 
assets in recent months to reduce debt 
in its fiscal year ended june 30 bond corp lost 9802 million 
australian dollars the largest annual loss in australian corporate 
history 
bond corps g heileman brewing co unit in the united states 
so far is not involved in the receivership proceedings 
heileman spokesman bill eiler said in a telephone interview from 
pittsburgh thursday the us brewer has separate financing from 
bond corp and as a matter of policy does not comment on matters 
involving bond 
bond purchased la crosse wisbased heileman in 1987 for about 
13 billion and reportedly still owes about 850 million after 
selling the profitable heileman baking co and other heileman 
subsidiaries 
heileman officials said recently they have been meeting with 
creditors and reviewing alternatives aimed at favorably modifying 
heilemans existing debt structure 
separately adolph coors co the fourthlargest us brewing 
company acknowledged this week it has held talks with heileman for 
over a year about the possible purchase of the wisconsin brewer 
</TEXT>
